{
  "stem": "3360.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When I could not go because I would have a bad cold or I'd have some kind-- I was sick, I would actually cry because I did-- I would-- I preferred to be in school.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's how much I liked it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was from 1930 to '34.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had-- [CLEARING THROAT] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had little, we had little crocheting and stitching circles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the mothers would fix some sweets for us and lemonade to drink.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had a lot of homework, always, so that kept us busy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after the homework, probably play on the street or have a friend over to play some games, depending on the season.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we had-- we did field trips.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we learned a lot about Hamburg and its surrounding area.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We went to the harbor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We found out what, what the ships that came to Hamburg would, would take on for freight or what they would deliver for freight-- freighters.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And of course, there was a big, there was still a very big traffic in Atlantic crossings, because this was really before the era of the commercial flight across the Atlantic.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so we, we would walk home together partly, for wherever we needed-- wherever our homes were.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Partly we would walk together, and then, you know, then you'd have to go on on your own and wind up walking by yourself to your own place.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But one, one thing that comes to mind that-- [CLEARING THROAT] Excuse me-- I remember is, the year before, or the months before Hitler actually came to power in 1933, things were terribly bad in Germany.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, they were bad in the '20s already.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was born into one of the worst inflations that ever existed in the entire world economy, I guess.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
